        <div class="span6">
            <h2>Download Data</h2>
            <p>Download data via the API by making a standard HTTP request to this URL:
                <pre>http://data.vehiclefits.com/api/download?token=<?=$this->api_token?></pre></p>
            <p>The API token is required to download data. Data will be returned to you in CSV format</p>

        </div><!--/span-->

        <div class="span6">
            <h2>Upload</h2>
            <p>
                To upload data anonymously via the API, make a POST request to the following URL:
                <pre>http://data.vehiclefits.com/api/upload</pre>
            </p>
            <p>
                The body of your POST request should be a CSV file with field names. You may specify any field names, however if you can match the exact field names we use that is preferable!
            </p>
            <p>
                If you want your uploaded files to be associated to your user account, pass your API token in the URL
                <pre>http://data.vehiclefits.com/api/upload?token=<?=$this->api_token?></pre>
            </p>
            <p>
                We will respond to your upload request with an ID corresponding to your upload. If we add an API in the future for checking the status of your upload, the ID will be used. If we respond 0, it is because we didn't receive any POST data from you.
            </p>
        </div><!--/span-->
